ment/bollywood/after-shaandaar-debacle-vikas-bahl-still-raring-to-go/ | accessdate=30 November 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"IBNLive 2015\">{{cite web | title=In 'Shaandaar', the sense of humour did not work with people; only I found it funny, says director Vikas Bahl | publisher=CNN-IBN | date=25 November 2015 | url=http://www.ibnlive.com/news/movies/in-shaandaar-the-sense-of-humour-did-not-work-with-people-only-i-found-it-funny-says-director-vikas-bahl-1168483.html | accessdate=30 November 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"India Today 2015\">{{cite web | title=After Shaandaar debacle, Shahid and Mira to dance at Madhu-Masaba's sangeet? : Celebrities, News | website=India Today | date=14 November 2015 | url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/after-shaandaar-debacle-shahid-and-mira-to-dance-at-madhu-masabas-sangeet/1/522834.html | accessdate=30 November 2015}}</ref> The success of [[Pyaar Ka Punchnama 2]] was considered to add to the film's failure.<ref name=\"dna 2015\">{{cite web | title=Did 'Pyaar ka Punchnama 2' prove detrimental to 'Shaandaar' and 'Main Aur Charles'? | website=dna | date=31 October 2015 | url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-did-pyaar-ka-punchnama-2-prove-detrimental-to-shaandaar-and-main-aur-charles-2140648 | accessdate=30 November 2015}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|4007558}}\n\n{{Karan Johar}}\n{{Dharma Productions}}\n{{Anurag Kashyap}}\n\n[[Category:Films about Indian weddings]]\n[[Category:Films shot in England]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2010s Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:2015 films]]\n[[Category:Indian romantic comedy films]]\n[[Category:2010s romantic comedy films]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Amit Trivedi]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Mikey McCleary]]\n[[Category:Fox Star Studios films]]\n[[Category:Indian films with live action and animation]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2015 film by Vikas Bahl}}\n{{about||the 1974 release|Shaandaar (1974 film)|the 1990 release|Shandaar}}\n{{EngvarB|date=September 2017}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2017}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Shaandaar\n| alt            =\n| image          = Shaandaar-Official-Poster-2.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Vikas Bahl]]\n| producer       = [[Anurag Kashyap]]<br />[[Vikramaditya Motwane]]<br />[[Karan Johar]]<br />[[Madhu Mantena]]\n| writer         = [[Anvita Dutt Guptan]]\n| story          = Vikas Bahl<br />Chaitally Parmar\n| starring       = [[Shahid Kapoor]]<br />[[Alia Bhatt]]\n| music          = [[Amit Trivedi]]\n| cinematography = [[Anil Mehta]]\n| editing        = Sanchari Das Mollick\n| studio         = [[Phantom Films]]<br />Dharma Productions\n| distributor    = [[Fox Star Studios]]\n| released       = {{Film date|df=yes|2015|10|22}}\n| runtime        =  144 minutes\n| country        = India\n| language       = Hindi\n| budget         = <!--Must be supported by a reliable published source with a reputation for fact-checking. No blogs. See WP:RS--> {{INR}}690 million<ref name=\"boxofficeindia.com\">{{cite web|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/movie.php?movieid=3099|title=Shaandaar \u2013 Movie \u2013 Box Office India|website=boxofficeindia.com}}</ref>\n| gross          = <!--Do not remove-->{{Estimation}}<!--per discussion at WP:ICTF--> {{INR}}757 million <ref name=\"boxofficeindia.com\" />\n}}\n'''''Shaandaar''''' ({{translation|Magnificent}}) is a 2015 [[Cinema of India|Indian]] [[romantic comedy]] film, directed by [[Vikas Bahl]] and produced by [[Anurag Kashyap]] and [[Vikramaditya Motwane]]. It stars [[Shahid Kapoor]] and [[Alia Bhatt]] in lead roles, with [[Pankaj Kapur]] and [[Sanjay Kapoor]] in supporting roles.<ref>{{cite news|last=Gupta|first=Priya|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Sanjay-Kapoor-joins-the-Shaandar-wedding-in-UK/articleshow/41099392.cms|title=Sanjay Kapoor joins the Shaandar wedding in UK|work=The Times of India|date=29 August 2014|accessdate=7 September 2014}}</ref> ''[[The Times of India]]'' described ''Shaandar'' as \"India's first [[destination wedding]] film\". Principal photography began in August 2014 in [[Leeds]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Check out: Shahid Kapoor and Alia Bhatt on sets of Shaandar|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/7114|publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]]|date=1 September 2014|accessdate=7 September 2014}}</ref> and the film released on 22 October 2015.<ref>{{cite news|last=Harikumar|first=Sumbramanian|url=http://www.bollywoodlife.com/south-gossip/shahid-kapoor-and-alia-bhatts-shaandaar-to-release-on-october-22-2015/|title=Shahid Kapoor- Alia Bhatt's Shaandaar to release on October 22nd|work=Bollywood Life|date=25 June 2015|accessdate=25 June 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nAlia Arora ([[Alia Bhatt]]) is an orphan who is adopted by Bipin Arora ([[Pankaj Kapur]]) whose wife Geetu Arora ([[Niki Aneja Walia]]) and mother Kamla Arora ([[Sushma Seth]]) are extremely business minded and have no feeling except for money. Alia is hated by Geetu and Kamla but is loved by Bipin and his daughter Isha (Sanah Kapoor). Alia is also an insomniac whom Bipin encourages to sleep by giving dreams drawn on paper but doesn't succeed.\n\nThe girls grow and while driving to the palatial wedding place for Isha, Bipin's car is hit by Jagjinder Joginder aka JJ ([[Shahid Kapoor]]) driving his motorcycle and abuses him comically, and is later revealed to be the event manager for Isha's marriage. The marriage is being arranged as a business merger between the Fundwanis led by Mr Fundwani ([[Sanjay Kapoor]]) and Aroras. The bride groom Robin Fundwani ([[Vikas Verma]]) is a fitness freak and is obsessed with his abs; he looks at Isha with contempt because she is chubby and loves eating food. Through some magical and comical moments Alia and JJ (who is also an insomniac due to loss of his mother in riots) get attracted to each other and finding peace among each other end up sleeping and thus curing their insomnia. Kamla has a sneezing accident and dies. But the Aroras are desperate for the marriage as they are bankrupt and really need the money from the merger of the two families.\n\nRobin on the other hand escalates the friction by verbally abusing Isha at many instances leading to Isha breaking her marriage off at the wedding dais and her speech inspires every one to believe in themselves and their real inner self. Frustrated Fundwani tries to physically force the marriage through and it is revealed that the Fundwanis are bankrupt too. JJ, Alia, Bipin, Isha and Robin escape from the scene and fly off to a happy ending.\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Shahid Kapoor]] as Jagjinder Joginder(JJ)-Alia\u2019s boyfriend. (Event manager)\n*[[Alia Bhatt]] as Alia Arora, Joginder-Bipin and Prabha\u2019s daughter, Isha\u2019s half sister, Jagjinder\u2019s girlfriend.\n*Sanah Kapur as Isha Arora-Bipin and Geetu\u2019s daughter, Alia\u2019s half sister, Robin\u2019s fiancee.\n*[[Vikas Verma]] as Robin Fundwani- Mr. Fundwani\u2019s brother, Isha\u2019s fiance, Bipin\u2019s to be son-in-law.\n*[[Pankaj Kapur]] as Bipin Arora- Geetu and Prabha\u2019s husband, Isha and Alia\u2019s father\n*[[Sanjay Kapoor]] as Mr. Fundwani-Robin\u2019s brother.\n*[[Niki Aneja Walia]] as Geetu Arora-Bipin\u2019s wife, Isha\u2019s mother, Alia\u2019s step mother. \n*[[Sushma Seth]] as Kamla Arora-Bipin\u2019s mother, Geetu and Prabha\u2019s  mother-in-law of Geetu, Isha and Alia\u2019s grandmother.(dead)\n*[[Shibani Dandekar]] as Sonia-assistant event manager.\n*[[Anjana Sukhani]] as Mrs. Fundwani-Mr. Fundwani\u2019s wife.\n*[[Karan Johar]] as Himself.\n*Tessa Vellara and Teena Vellara as the Twins.\n*[[Shalini Chandran]] as Relative.\n* Hagupreet Singh as Robin's friend and Karan Johar's love interest.\n* Kumud Pant as Business Wedding Guest.\n\n== Critical reception==\nDeepanjana Pal at ''[[Firstpost]]'' described the writing as sloppy, commenting that, \"it's more a series of YouTube sketches than a proper story.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Shaandaar review: Alia Bhatt, Shahid Kapoor look great, but this film is far from fabulous|url=http://www.firstpost.com/bollywood/shaandaar-review-alia-bhatt-shahid-kapoor-look-great-but-this-film-is-far-from-fabulous-2478624.html|publisher=firstpost.com|accessdate=22 October 2015}}</ref> ''[[Indian Express]]'' felt that Kapoor's character Jagjinder Joginder was \"badly-written\", noting, \"He can be such a natural charmer, but here the charm offensive is not allowed to stop, and finally just overtakes him.\"<ref name=IEShaandaar>{{cite web|title=Shaandaar review: There is no 'Shaan' in this Shahid Kapoor, Alia Bhatt starrer|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/shaandaar-review/|website=The Indian Express|accessdate=22 October 2015}}</ref> Saibal Chatterjee of [[NDTV]], felt that while there were \"flashes of smart writing\", that there was also \"[a lack] of sustained narrative force, especially in the second half\". Chatterjee described the interaction between Kapoor and Bhatt as \"spontaneous chemistry\", an opinion that was not shared by the ''Indian Express'' reviewer, who wrote, \"Shahid and Alia look good together, but there's not very much else they manage between the two of them.\"<ref name=IEShaandaar />\n\nIbnlive described the movie as \"The film is bizarre and wildly inconsistent\".<ref>{{Cite web|title = 'Shaandaar' review: The film is bizarre and wildly inconsistent|url = http://www.ibnlive.com/news/movies/shaandaar-review-the-film-is-bizarre-and-wildly-inconsistent-1155213.html|publisher = CNN-IBN|accessdate = 13 November 2015}}</ref> [[India TV]] stated \"There is nothing Shaandaar about this Shahid-Alia starrer\".<ref>{{Cite web|title = Shaandaar Review: There is nothing Shaandaar about this Shahid-Alia starrer|url = http://www.indiatvnews.com/entertainment/bollywood/shandaar-movie-review-24775.html|website = India TV News|accessdate = 13 November 2015}}</ref> TimesofIndia gave two stars to the film.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Shaandaar Movie Review, Trailer, & Show timings at Times of India|url = http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-reviews/Shaandaar/movie-review/49494611.cms|website = The Times of India|accessdate = 13 November 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Shaandaar\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| artist     = [[Amit Trivedi]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = {{Start date|df=yes|2015|09|24}}\n| recorded   = 2015\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Film soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = {{Duration|m=32|s=06}}\n| language   = [[Hindi language|Hindi]]\n| label      = [[Zee Music Company]]\n| producer   =\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Shaandaar\n | type        = Soundtrack\n | single1     = Gulaabo\n | single1date = 10 September 2015<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/in/album/gulaabo-from-shaandaar-single/id1038056339| title =Gulaabo (From \"Shaandaar\") \u2013 Single| publisher = [[iTunes Store]] }}</ref>\n | single2     = Shaam Shaandaar\n | single2date = 16 September 2015<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/shaam-shaandaar-from-shaandaar/id1040405793| title =Shaam Shaandaar (From \"Shaandaar\") \u2013 Single| publisher = [[iTunes Store]]}}</ref>\n}}\n}}\nThe music and background score for the film is composed by [[Amit Trivedi]]<ref>[http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/gulaabo-alia-shahid-first-song-from-film-is-a-shaandaar-party-number/1/470183.html Gulaabo: Alia-Shahid's first song from film is a Shaandaar party number : Bollywood, News \u2013 India Today]. ''India Today''.intoday.in (10 September 2015). Retrieved 24 September 2015.</ref> The first song titled, \"''Gulaabo''\" was released on 10 September 2015,<ref>[https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/gulaabo-from-shaandaar-single/id1038056339?ign-mpt=uo%3D8 Gulaabo (From \"Shaandaar\") \u